      "message": "https://screenshot.googleplex.com/kuqHFihNFbi\n\nHaving gone back and forth on timestamps with other people for a long time, and 100% this will cause confusion and frustration for users to not be able to tell at a glance what timezone the timestamps are in.\n\nGiven any timestamp, anyone should be able to tell unambiguously at a glance what timezone that timestamp is a part of.  Without the timezone stamp, timestamps become more ambiguous.\n\nAnother way to do that could be to add the (z)/(PST)/(CEST) to the \"Finished Time\" header column, and then the (z) wouldn\u0027t have to repeat.",
